You are in the review lane. Files here implement exactly-once backfill, reconciliation,
and cutover — the product's entire credibility.

- Keep diffs small and single-purpose; do not combine a core change with refactors.
- Before declaring done: run `make test` AND `make crash`; paste both summaries.
- State in your final message: which invariant(s) (I1–I13) the change touches, and
  which property test or crash scenario now covers it. If none does, write that test
  first.
- Flag explicitly that this diff requires the P8 adversarial review (PROMPTS.md) before
  merge — do not mark the task complete without saying so.
- Any ordering change around claim → embed → upsert → ledger/checkpoint must include a
  comment citing I2 and explaining why durability-before-progress still holds.
